TY  - JOUR
T1  - Evolutionary Trajectories in Petroleum Firm R&D
AU  - Helfat, Constance E.
Y1  - 1994/12/01
PY  - 1994
DA  - 1994/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.40.12.1720
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.40.12.1720
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1720
EP  - 1747
VL  - 40
IS  - 12
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Tacit knowledge and cumulative learning underlie an evolutionary theory of business firm development and strategy. As one test case of the theory, this study examines firms' applied research and development activities. Evolutionary theory suggests that firms within an industry will tend both to persist and to differ in the amount of effort they devote to various R&D applications. A test of the hypothesis of presistent differences in R&D, using uniquely detailed data from the petroleum industry, provides support for evolutionary theory.
AB  - Tacit knowledge and cumulative learning underlie an evolutionary theory of business firm development and strategy. As one test case of the theory, this study examines firms' applied research and development activities. Evolutionary theory suggests that firms within an industry will tend both to persist and to differ in the amount of effort they devote to various R&D applications. A test of the hypothesis of presistent differences in R&D, using uniquely detailed data from the petroleum industry, provides support for evolutionary theory.
